crawlercommons.fetcher.http

Class UserAgent

  • java.lang.Object
    • crawlercommons.fetcher.http.UserAgent
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable
    Deprecated. 
    As of release 0.6. We recommend directly using Apache HttpClient, async-http-client, or any other robust, industrial-strength HTTP clients.

    @Deprecated
public class UserAgent
extends Object
implements Serializable
    User Agent enables us to describe characteristics of any Crawler Commons agent. There are a number of constructor options to describe the following:
    1. _agentName: Primary agent name.
    2. _emailAddress: The agent owners email address.
    3. _webAddress: A web site/address representing the agent owner.
    4. _browserVersion: Broswer version used for compatibility.
    5. _crawlerVersion: Version of the user agents personal crawler. If this is not set, it defaults to the crawler commons maven artifact version.
    See Also:
